The paper deals with the design and analysis of auctions, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The construction of the auction involves polynomial time algorithms, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the adoption of a finer lens of competitiveness, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and complexity theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of auctions, which is a topic in economics (cs.EC).
